conomic thinker. Close readings of Milton's prose and verse reveal the importance of economic ideas in a wide range of his most famous writings, from Areopagitica to Samson Agonistes to Paradise Lost.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCommerce dans la littérature. 0aCommerce in literature. 0aEconomics and literaturexHistoryx17th centuryxGreat Britain. 0aEconomics and literaturezGreat BritainxHistoryy17th century. 0aEconomics in literature. 0aÉconomie politique dans la littérature. 0aÉconomie politique et littératurexHistoirex17e sièclexGrande-Bretagne. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300129632423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300129632.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles